---
<Layout title="Leadership | Professor Iain Rice">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Leadership" title="Academic, organisational and AI transformation leadership." lede="A track record of leading people, programmes and AI systems in complex, regulated and diverse environments." />
  <section class="section"><div class="container grid-2">
    <div class="card"><h3>Birmingham City University</h3><p>Professor of Industrial AI, Professor of AI and Head of Teaching & Learning. Leading teaching and learning activity, supervising applied AI research, directing consultancy projects and leading a team of over 100 academic staff.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Strategic AI leadership</h3><p>Managed projects from £55k to over £3m with multiple stakeholders and regulatory reporting mechanisms. Designed and managed a conversion MSc Artificial Intelligence course attracting over 2000 applications in three years.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>External advisory roles</h3><p>Chief Data Scientist with Our Safer City, working alongside City of London Police on predictive analytics and dashboards to help prevent violence against women and girls.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>FinTech and education innovation</h3><p>AI Advisor to Figg Wealth on AI strategy, LLM integration and predictive analytics. Head of Content with Bot Theory, developing bite-size education activities in web-3.0 enabled game environments.</p></div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="section dark"><div class="container"><h2>Previous leadership</h2><p>At Arden University, led Computing & IT with a £4m budget line and 40 staff internationally, growing Data MSc offerings to net £1m annually within two years and developing apprenticeship offerings across technology and management disciplines.</p></div></section>
</Layout>
